    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Cylinder Head Inspection - Valves Installed</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Cylinder head condition must be evaluated by inspecting for thickness, warping, cracks, and valve
                    leakage.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300536" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0868.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measuring the cylinder head thickness</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To determine if cylinder head has been resurfaced previously, use a 3-4 inch micrometer to
                measure cylinder head deck thickness at four corner locations. If overall cylinder head thickness
                (deck-to-deck) specification is not met, replace cylinder head. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_114.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300537" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08046.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking for gasket surface flatness</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a straightedge and feeler gauge to check cylinder head gasket surface for flatness.
                Check for flatness horizontally, diagonally, and transversely. If specifications are not met, replace
                cylinder head. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_114.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300538" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking valve recession</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve head</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before removing valves, check valve head recession (relative to deck) as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a straightedge across each valve.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a feeler gauge between straightedge and valve head. Record valve recession
                    clearance.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If out of specification, replace valve. Perform step 2 over again, and if specifications
                    are still not met, replace cylinder head. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_114.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect for cracks in the cylinder head using the Dye Penetrant Kit. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_116.xml" xrefid="E30005C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="e300539" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0832.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Spraying cleaner on cylinder head</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Spray cleaner on gasket surface of cylinder head and wipe dry.</para>
                <figure id="e300540" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0833.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Spraying Dye Penetrant onto cylinder head</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Spray dye penetrant onto gasket surface of cylinder head. Allow dye to remain on surface
                    from 1 to 30 minutes.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Wipe dye off cylinder head surface.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Dye will remain in any cracks during this 'wipe off' step.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="e300541" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0888.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Spraying developer onto cylinder head</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="e300542" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0835.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Cylinder head crack between intake and exhaust valves</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Spray developer on gasket surface of cylinder head and let dry for 5 to 15 minutes.
                    Cracks will show up as purple lines against white developer.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, replace the cylinder head if any cracks are present.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check for valve leakage using mineral spirits as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position cylinder head on wooden blocks with gasket surface facing down.</para>
                <figure id="e300543" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0839.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Squirting ports with mineral spirits</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Squirt mineral spirits in intake and exhaust ports.</para>
                <figure id="e300544" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0840.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Inspecting for leaks</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Inspection mirror</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Reflection of valve</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Flashlight</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Wait five minutes. Use an inspection mirror to inspect valve seat area for leakage of
                    mineral spirits.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There should be no leakage. Valve seat reconditioning is not required if the cylinder head passes
                    the mineral spirits test. If leakage is observed, the valves require reconditioning.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcsubproc>
